    <div class="docback">
     <div class="note-source" id="PJA08d094sn1">
      <p>
       <span class="docSource"><span class="dType"><abbr title="fade=[ on ] fadespeed=[0.1] windowlock=[on] cssbody=[ boxover ] header=[]  body=[ recipients copy (A recipients copy is assumed to be in the hand of the signer unless it is otherwise described.) ]">RC</abbr></span> (<span class="ref-terms">Adams Papers</span>); docketed: Mr. Chase; by <abbr title="fade=[ on ] fadespeed=[0.1] windowlock=[on] cssbody=[ boxover ] header=[]  body=[ Charles Francis Adams (18071886), son of John Quincy Adams and Louisa Catherine Adams ]">CFA</abbr>: Septr. 3d 1779. On the blank fourth page of Chases letter is the draft of <abbr title="fade=[ on ] fadespeed=[0.1] windowlock=[on] cssbody=[ boxover ] header=[]  body=[ John Adams (17351826) ]">JA</abbr>s reply of <a href="default.xqy?keys=ADMS-print-06-08-02-0117" class="document">23 Sept.</a> (below).</span>
      </p>
     </div>
     <div id="fn" class="footnote"><a class="note-ref" href="#PJA08d094n1-ptr" id="PJA08d094n1">1</a>
